rComments: Great prof. Writes his own tests and tells you exactly what you need to know. If you can take decent notes his tests are easy. But he does talk fast. Dont even bother trying to write your notes. Bring a laptop! First prof I have had that actually asks us for feedback. He literally changed the entire exam because we asked him to!
teacherRatingTags: ["Skip class? You won't pass.", 'Participation matters', 'Group projects']

rComments: Appreciate his effort on making the powerpoints and an anonymous google feedback form (for improvements in class contents), but I guess students want to submit the google form and have improvements for the current class not the future one. He always says he can only do it for next year, but I know some profs change the syllabus during the term.

His tests emphasized too much on memorization - what's the point of it? No application of the theory at all. When I flipped the midterm over I just feel like he wants us to be a human dictionary. Upper level management courses shouldn't be like that. We're not first years anymore and the course should be well-structured and applicable.

Anthony is the best! He really cares about his students getting good grades. He often asked the lass how and what he could do to make the class better. He did not force his learning style on us which I thought was great! If you go to class, you will do fine but be prepared to type fast

Amazing Prof. You don't have to read the book if you take good notes during class time, but you have to type fast as the lecture is only for an hour and then for the other hour it's a case. Make sure you read the case before hand and participate at least once because participation is 10%.
teacherRatingTags: ["Skip class? You won't pass.", 'Lecture heavy', 'Gives good feedback']
